      },
      "date": "2018-04-11 11:08:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe refcount leakage should have been fixed by https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/31143/.\n\nActually in the first implementation of cached remote lock, it doesn't pin object, but Alex thought this is too efficient to lookup by fid each time, and though cached remote lock is only  used by ROOT xattr lock now, it's a general infrastructure, and can be used in other places if remote lock is frequently requested.\n\nIn summary, it's not an issue that ldlm lock pins object, but it should guarantee there is no race in object release.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
