          "date": "2018-04-10 03:53:43.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-10887 mdt: ldlm lock should not pin object",
        "message": "LU-10887 mdt: ldlm lock should not pin object\n\nFor performance, the MDT needs to cache remote ROOT xattr\nwith holding xattr ldlm lock. Originally, such xattr ldlm\nlock directly back references the object via l_ast_data.\nThat pins the object in RAM. Unfortunately, such reference\nmay prevent the ROOT object being released when umount MDT:\n\nkernel: LustreError: 49321:0:(osp_dev.c:1276:osp_device_free())\nheader@ffff885e724737b0[0x0, 1, [0x200000007:0x1:0x0] hash exist]{\nkernel: LustreError: 49321:0:(osp_dev.c:1276:osp_device_free())\n....mdt@ffff885e72473800mdt-object@ffff885e724737b0( , writecount=0)\n\nThis patch drops such back reference. Instead, we can locate\nthe object with its FID when need to invalid the cache.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iec0d61c76fbff636c7fbbffc00648c6751c0a051\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
